c:T7d8,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does coastal erosion affect water damage in Redondo Beach?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Coastal erosion along Redondo Beach's shoreline accelerates during winter storms, undermining foundations of beachfront properties and causing structural damage. The King Harbor area is particularly vulnerable to wave action that can flood lower floors and damage docks and boat-related infrastructure."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What flood risks exist near King Harbor?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"King Harbor experiences flooding during storm events when wave action combines with high tides. Marina structures and adjacent commercial properties face significant water damage risks, with floodwaters commonly reaching parking areas and ground-floor commercial spaces."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are Redondo Beach homes required to have flood insurance?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Properties in FEMA flood zones AE and VE near the coastline are required to carry flood insurance. Many homeowners in King Harbor and beachfront areas maintain coverage due to the high risk of storm surge and coastal flooding events."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does the proximity to the Pacific Ocean affect basements in Redondo Beach?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Redondo Beach has very few basements due to the high water table and proximity to the ocean. Ground-level flooding from storm surge and rain events can enter homes through foundations and doorways rather than basement windows."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What water damage risks exist from the nearby AES power plant site?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The former AES power plant site near the harbor is a remediated wetland area that can experience localized flooding during heavy rains, potentially affecting adjacent properties with water accumulation and moisture issues."}}]}2:[["$","section",null,{"className":"py-16 md:py-24","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6","children":[["$","$L8",null,{"href":"/","className":"hover:text-white","children":"Home"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-2","children":"/"}],["$","$L8",null,{"href":"/locations","className":"hover:text-white","children":"Locations"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-2","children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Redondo Beach"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4","children":["Water Damage Restoration in ",["$","span",null,{"className":"text-blue-500","children":["Redondo Beach",", ","CA"]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-3xl","children":["Professional water damage restoration services in ","Redondo Beach",". Our certified technicians provide fast, reliable service when you need it most."]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mb-12","children":[["$","a",null,{"href":"tel:+18885109436","className":"flex items-center justify-center space-x-2 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 px-8 py-4 rounded-lg text-lg font-semibold transition-colors","children":[["$","svg",null,{"className":"w-6 h-6","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","viewBox":"0 0 24 24","children":["$","path",null,{"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","strokeWidth":2,"d":"M3 5a2 2 0 012-2h3.28a1 1 0 01.948.684l1.498 4.493a1 1 0 01-.502 1.21l-2.257 1.13a11.042 11.042 0 005.516 5.516l1.13-2.257a1 1 0 011.21-.502l4.493 1.498a1 1 0 01.684.949V19a2 2 0 01-2 2h-1C9.716 21 3 14.284 3 6V5z"}]}],["$","span",null,{"children":"Call (888) 510-9436"}]]}],["$","$L8",null,{"href":"/contact","className":"flex items-center justify-center space-x-2 border border-blue-500 text-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-500 hover:text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg text-lg font-semibold transition-colors","children":["$","